{
  "video_id": "2vE-elqTGlQ",
  "title": "The stories behind The New Yorker's iconic covers | Fran√ßoise Mouly",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12580.0,
      "end_time": 14356.0,
      "text": "So 24 years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 14380.0,
      "end_time": 16156.0,
      "text": "I was brought to The New Yorker"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 16180.0,
      "end_time": 17700.0,
      "text": "as art editor"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 18300.0,
      "end_time": 21836.0,
      "text": "to rejuvenate"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 21860.0,
      "end_time": 26875.0,
      "text": "what had by then become a somewhat staid institution"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 26900.0,
      "end_time": 29395.0,
      "text": "and to bring in new artists"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 29420.0,
      "end_time": 33116.0,
      "text": "and to try to bring the magazine from its ivory tower"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 33140.0,
      "end_time": 36476.0,
      "text": "into engaging with its time."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 36500.0,
      "end_time": 39196.0,
      "text": "And it was just the right thing for me to do"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 39220.0,
      "end_time": 43836.0,
      "text": "because I&#39;ve always been captivated by how an image can --"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 43860.0,
      "end_time": 45556.0,
      "text": "a simple drawing --"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 45580.0,
      "end_time": 50315.0,
      "text": "can cut through the torrent of images that we see every single day."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 50340.0,
      "end_time": 52796.0,
      "text": "How it can capture a moment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 52820.0,
      "end_time": 58360.0,
      "text": "how it can crystallize a social trend or a complex event"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 58600.0,
      "end_time": 63236.0,
      "text": "in a way that a lot of words wouldn&#39;t be able to do --"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 63260.0,
      "end_time": 67600.0,
      "text": "and reduce it to its essence and turn it into a cartoon."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 67620.0,
      "end_time": 69396.0,
      "text": "So I went to the library"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 69420.0,
      "end_time": 75356.0,
      "text": "and I looked at the first cover drawn by Rea Irvin in 1925 --"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 75380.0,
      "end_time": 79780.0,
      "text": "a dandy looking at a butterfly through his monocle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 80580.0,
      "end_time": 83340.0,
      "text": "and we call it Eustace Tilley."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 83900.0,
      "end_time": 87916.0,
      "text": "And I realized that as the magazine had become known"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 87940.0,
      "end_time": 93396.0,
      "text": "for its in-depth research and long reports,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 93420.0,
      "end_time": 96356.0,
      "text": "some of the humor had gotten lost along the way,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 96380.0,
      "end_time": 101276.0,
      "text": "because now often Eustace Tilley was seen as a haughty dandy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 101300.0,
      "end_time": 104396.0,
      "text": "but in fact, in 1925,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 104420.0,
      "end_time": 107836.0,
      "text": "when Rea Irvin first drew this image,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 107860.0,
      "end_time": 110636.0,
      "text": "he did it as part of a humor magazine"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 110660.0,
      "end_time": 112875.0,
      "text": "to amuse the youth of the era,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 112900.0,
      "end_time": 115980.0,
      "text": "which was the flappers of the roaring twenties."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 116900.0,
      "end_time": 118156.0,
      "text": "And in the library,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 118180.0,
      "end_time": 123116.0,
      "text": "I found the images that really captured the zeitgeist"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 123140.0,
      "end_time": 125556.0,
      "text": "of the Great Depression."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 125580.0,
      "end_time": 129996.0,
      "text": "And it showed us not just how people dressed"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 130199.99999999999,
      "end_time": 131556.0,
      "text": "or what their cars looked like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 131580.0,
      "end_time": 134836.0,
      "text": "but also what made them laugh,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 134860.0,
      "end_time": 137156.0,
      "text": "what their prejudices were."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 137180.0,
      "end_time": 139756.0,
      "text": "And you really got a sense"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 139780.0,
      "end_time": 143260.0,
      "text": "of what it felt like to be alive in the &#39;30s."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 143780.0,
      "end_time": 147156.0,
      "text": "So I called on contemporary artists,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 147180.0,
      "end_time": 149396.0,
      "text": "such as Adrian Tomine here."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 149420.0,
      "end_time": 152555.0,
      "text": "I often call on narrative artists --"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 152580.0,
      "end_time": 155236.0,
      "text": "cartoonists, children&#39;s book authors --"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 155260.0,
      "end_time": 157780.0,
      "text": "and I give them themes such as,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 158660.0,
      "end_time": 160996.0,
      "text": "you know, what it&#39;s like to be in the subway,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 161200.0,
      "end_time": 163196.0,
      "text": "or Valentine&#39;s Day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 163220.0,
      "end_time": 164596.0,
      "text": "and they send me sketches."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 164620.0,
      "end_time": 168516.0,
      "text": "And once the sketches are approved by the editor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 168540.0,
      "end_time": 169900.0,
      "text": "David Remnick,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 171600.0,
      "end_time": 173156.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s a go."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 173180.0,
      "end_time": 175156.0,
      "text": "And I love the way"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 175180.0,
      "end_time": 180436.0,
      "text": "those images are actually not telling you what to think."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 180460.0,
      "end_time": 182676.0,
      "text": "But they do make you think,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 182700.0,
      "end_time": 187715.0,
      "text": "because the artist is actually --"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 187740.0,
      "end_time": 188996.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s almost a puzzle;"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 189200.0,
      "end_time": 190516.0,
      "text": "the artist is drawing the dots,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 190540.0,
      "end_time": 194236.0,
      "text": "and you, the reader, have to complete the picture."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 194260.0,
      "end_time": 197636.0,
      "text": "So to get this image on the left by Anita Kunz,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 197660.0,
      "end_time": 200716.0,
      "text": "or the one on right by Tomer Hanuka,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 200740.0,
      "end_time": 203876.0,
      "text": "you have to play spot the differences."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 203900.0,
      "end_time": 206820.0,
      "text": "And it is something that ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 207540.0,
      "end_time": 211236.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s really exciting to see"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 211260.0,
      "end_time": 217316.0,
      "text": "how the engagement with the reader ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 217340.0,
      "end_time": 222276.0,
      "text": "how those images really capture --"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 222300.0,
      "end_time": 223836.0,
      "text": "play with the stereotypes."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 223860.0,
      "end_time": 225236.0,
      "text": "But when you get it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 225260.0,
      "end_time": 228820.0,
      "text": "it rearranges the stereotypes that are in your head."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 229380.0,
      "end_time": 232676.0,
      "text": "But the images don&#39;t just have to show people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 232700.0,
      "end_time": 235360.0,
      "text": "sometimes it can be a feeling."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 235600.0,
      "end_time": 237100.0,
      "text": "Right after September 11,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 237940.0,
      "end_time": 240596.0,
      "text": "I was at a point,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 240620.0,
      "end_time": 241836.0,
      "text": "like everybody else,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 241860.0,
      "end_time": 247760.0,
      "text": "where I really didn&#39;t know how to deal with what we were going through,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 247100.0,
      "end_time": 252516.0,
      "text": "and I felt that no image could capture this moment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 252540.0,
      "end_time": 255360.0,
      "text": "and I wanted to just do a black cover,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 255600.0,
      "end_time": 256756.0,
      "text": "like no cover."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 256779.0,
      "end_time": 260476.0,
      "text": "And I talked to my husband, cartoonist Art Spiegelman,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 260500.0,
      "end_time": 264356.0,
      "text": "and mentioned to him that I was going to propose that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 264380.0,
      "end_time": 266956.0,
      "text": "and he said, \"Oh, if you&#39;re going to do a black cover,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 266980.0,
      "end_time": 270996.0,
      "text": "then why don&#39;t you do the silhouette of the Twin Towers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 271200.0,
      "end_time": 272556.0,
      "text": "black on black?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 272580.0,
      "end_time": 274116.0,
      "text": "And I sat down to draw this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 274140.0,
      "end_time": 275620.0,
      "text": "and as soon as I saw it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 276740.0,
      "end_time": 278276.0,
      "text": "a shiver ran down my spine"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 278300.0,
      "end_time": 279500.0,
      "text": "and I realized"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 280460.0,
      "end_time": 284116.0,
      "text": "that in this refusal to make an image,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 284140.0,
      "end_time": 289156.0,
      "text": "we had found a way to capture loss"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 289180.0,
      "end_time": 290676.0,
      "text": "and mourning"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 290700.0,
      "end_time": 291979.0,
      "text": "and absence."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 293700.0,
      "end_time": 298750.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s been a profound thing that I learned in the process --"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 298100.0,
      "end_time": 304360.0,
      "text": "that sometimes some of the images that say the most"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 304600.0,
      "end_time": 307140.0,
      "text": "do it with the most spare means."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 307700.0,
      "end_time": 311276.0,
      "text": "And a simple image can speak volumes."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 311300.0,
      "end_time": 314556.0,
      "text": "So this is the image that we published by Bob Staake"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 314580.0,
      "end_time": 318419.0,
      "text": "right after the election of Barack Obama,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 319860.0,
      "end_time": 323116.0,
      "text": "and captured a historic moment."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 323140.0,
      "end_time": 325356.0,
      "text": "But we can&#39;t really plan for this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 325380.0,
      "end_time": 326756.0,
      "text": "because in order to do this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 326780.0,
      "end_time": 333116.0,
      "text": "we have to let the artist experience the emotions that we all feel"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 333140.0,
      "end_time": 334620.0,
      "text": "when that is happening."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 335140.0,
      "end_time": 338955.0,
      "text": "So back in November 2016,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 338980.0,
      "end_time": 341756.0,
      "text": "during the election last year,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 341780.0,
      "end_time": 344916.0,
      "text": "the only image that we could publish was this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 344940.0,
      "end_time": 348876.0,
      "text": "which was on the stand on the week that everybody voted."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 348900.0,
      "end_time": 350236.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 350260.0,
      "end_time": 352716.0,
      "text": "Because we knew somebody would feel this --"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 352740.0,
      "end_time": 353956.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 353980.0,
      "end_time": 356660.0,
      "text": "when the result of the election was announced."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 358180.0,
      "end_time": 361140.0,
      "text": "And when we found out the result,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 362420.0,
      "end_time": 364276.0,
      "text": "we really were at a loss,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 364300.0,
      "end_time": 370316.0,
      "text": "and this is the image that was sent by Bob Staake again,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 370340.0,
      "end_time": 373380.0,
      "text": "and that really hit a chord."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 374100.0,
      "end_time": 375356.0,
      "text": "And again,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 375380.0,
      "end_time": 381836.0,
      "text": "we can&#39;t really figure out what&#39;s going to come next,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 381860.0,
      "end_time": 384556.0,
      "text": "but here it felt like we didn&#39;t know how to move forward,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 384580.0,
      "end_time": 386360.0,
      "text": "but we did move forward,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 386600.0,
      "end_time": 392276.0,
      "text": "and this is the image that we published after Donald Trump&#39;s election"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 392300.0,
      "end_time": 395716.0,
      "text": "and at the time of the Women&#39;s March"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 395740.0,
      "end_time": 397600.0,
      "text": "all over the US."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 397940.0,
      "end_time": 399796.0,
      "text": "So over those 24 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 399820.0,
      "end_time": 404596.0,
      "text": "I have seen over 1,000 images come to life week after week,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 404620.0,
      "end_time": 407196.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;m often asked which one is my favorite,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 407220.0,
      "end_time": 409760.0,
      "text": "but I can&#39;t pick one"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 409100.0,
      "end_time": 415360.0,
      "text": "because what I&#39;m most proud of is how different every image is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 415600.0,
      "end_time": 416276.0,
      "text": "one from the other."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 416300.0,
      "end_time": 419756.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s due to the talent and the diversity"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 419780.0,
      "end_time": 422739.0,
      "text": "of all of the artists that contribute."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 423420.0,
      "end_time": 425196.0,
      "text": "And now, well,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 425220.0,
      "end_time": 427760.0,
      "text": "now, we&#39;re owned by Russia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 427100.0,
      "end_time": 428316.0,
      "text": "so --"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 428340.0,
      "end_time": 429556.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 429580.0,
      "end_time": 432276.0,
      "text": "In a rendering by Barry Blitt here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 432300.0,
      "end_time": 437516.0,
      "text": "Eustace has become Eustace Vladimirovich Tilley."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 437540.0,
      "end_time": 442636.0,
      "text": "And the butterfly is none other than a flabbergasted Donald Trump"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 442660.0,
      "end_time": 443876.0,
      "text": "flapping his wings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 443900.0,
      "end_time": 447955.0,
      "text": "trying to figure out how to control the butterfly effect,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 447980.0,
      "end_time": 453556.0,
      "text": "and the famed logo that was drawn by Rae Irvin in 1925"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 453580.0,
      "end_time": 455180.0,
      "text": "is now in Cyrillic."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 455740.0,
      "end_time": 459996.0,
      "text": "So, what makes me really excited about this moment"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 460200.0,
      "end_time": 462780.0,
      "text": "is the way that ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 463820.0,
      "end_time": 468556.0,
      "text": "You know, free press is essential to our democracy."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 468580.0,
      "end_time": 472236.0,
      "text": "And we can see from the sublime to the ridiculous"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 472260.0,
      "end_time": 476676.0,
      "text": "that artists can capture what is going on"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 476700.0,
      "end_time": 479316.0,
      "text": "in a way that an artist"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 479340.0,
      "end_time": 484476.0,
      "text": "armed with just India ink and watercolor"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 484500.0,
      "end_time": 490476.0,
      "text": "can capture and enter into the cultural dialogue."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 490500.0,
      "end_time": 495476.0,
      "text": "It puts those artists at the center of that culture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 495500.0,
      "end_time": 498316.0,
      "text": "and that&#39;s exactly where I think they should be."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 498340.0,
      "end_time": 501739.0,
      "text": "Because the main thing we need right now is a good cartoon."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 502220.0,
      "end_time": 503436.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 503460.0,
      "end_time": 507940.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}